<h3 class="auk-h3">Arguments (Menu::Item)</h3>

<table class="auk-table">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Argument</th>
      <th>Type</th>
      <th>Possible values</th>
      <th>Description</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><code>@skin</code></td>
      <td>string</td>
      <td class="auk-table__col--3"><code>danger</code></td>
      <td>Determines the skin of the dropdown item.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code>@disabled</code></td>
      <td>boolean</td>
      <td class="auk-table__col--3"><code>false</code> (default) or <code>true</code></td>
      <td>Determines if the dropdown item is disabled.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code>@textOnly</code></td>
      <td>boolean</td>
      <td class="auk-table__col--3"><code>false</code> (default) or <code>true</code></td>
      <td>Determines if the dropdown item is shown as text-only.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p>The Item component also takes the same arguments as a native link-element (<code>@href</code>) or a LinkTo component (<code>@route</code>, <code>@model</code>, <code>@models</code>, etc.), but only if <code>@textOnly</code> is <code>false</code>.</p>